# Feature modules (`src/features`)

Vertical slices mirror `src/` layout per feature:

```
features/<name>/
  components/   # UI for this feature
  hooks/
  lib/          # data + domain helpers
  types/
  index.ts      # public API — relative re-exports only (no @/features/self in barrels)
```

## Global context (`src/context/`)

App-wide React providers live here, not under `features/`:

| Module               | Exports                                 |
| -------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| `auth-provider.tsx`  | `AuthProvider`, `useAuth`               |
| `theme-provider.tsx` | `AppThemeProvider`, `useAppColorScheme` |

Wire providers in `src/app/_layout.tsx` from `@/context/...`. Feature barrels may re-export hooks for convenience (`@/features/auth` still exposes `useAuth`).

## Rules

- **Routes stay thin** in `src/app/`; wire screens to `@/features/<name>`.
- **Cross-feature imports** only via the other feature's `index.ts`, not deep paths.
- **Barrel `index.ts`** re-exports use `./relative` paths — never `@/features/<same-feature>/...` (Metro cannot resolve self-aliases).
- **Global providers** → `src/context/`, not `features/*/context/`.
- **Feature-scoped providers** (screen orchestration) → `features/<name>/context/<name>/` — see `.cursor/rules/react-context-provider.mdc`.
- **Shared design system**: `src/components/ui/`, `src/components/icons/`.
- **Cross-cutting hooks** (use global context): `src/hooks/` — e.g. `use-github-access-token.ts`.
- **Infrastructure**: `src/lib/errors.ts`, `src/lib/utils.ts`, `src/utils/supabase.ts`.

